I have implemented the Elevator Simulator as requested. The solution runs with `bun` without any dependencies.

The key files created are:
1. `index.html`: Contains the core structure of the DOM, loading the scripts and styles. Info from `info.json` is included as a comment block at the top as requested.
2. `styles.css`: Uses plain CSS to implement visual layout (the 10-floor building, elevators inside shafts, buttons, active states, etc.).
3. `Elevator.ts`: Handles the logic and state for individual elevators (direction, door animations, which floors they are targeted to stop at).
4. `Building.ts`: Handles assigning floor requests to the "best" elevator (checking idle vs same direction vs queueing) and renders all the dynamic buttons for each floor and inside each elevator.
5. `script.ts`: Acts as the main entry point to initiate the building simulation on DOM content load.

You can serve it via:
```sh
bunx serve -p 8805
```

Or build it into the `dist/` folder via:
```sh
mkdir -p ./dist
bun build ./index.html --outdir ./dist
```
